---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout 
  title="vaLak" 
  description="A cybersecurity notebook by vaLak. Pentesting journey, CTF writeups, and daily cyber news - themed around the Death Note universe."
  extraCss={['/styles/home.css']}
>
  
  <main class="page-wrapper" id="main-content">

    <!-- ── Hero ── -->
    <section class="hero" aria-label="Introduction">
      <div class="hero-title-container">
        <h1 class="visually-hidden">The False Positive</h1>
        <img 
          src="/assets/The_False_Positive_removed_bg.png" 
          alt="The False Positive" 
          class="hero-title-graphic" 
          loading="eager"
        />
      </div>

      <div class="hero-quote-container">
        <blockquote class="hero-quote">
          &#8220;There is a 94% probability that the person reading this
          is trying to get better at hacking.&#8221;
        </blockquote>
        <p class="hero-quote-attr">&sim;&thinsp; L - The World's Greatest Detective</p>
      </div>

      <p class="hero-desc">
        A personal notebook built for the me who was navigating TryHackMe,
        HackTheBox, and the overwhelming world of ethical hacking. Every technique,
        every command, every case file - documented like evidence.
      </p>

      <div class="hero-cta">
        <a href="/pentest" class="btn btn-primary" id="hero-enter-btn">
          Open the Note
          <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" aria-hidden="true">
            <path d="M5 12h14M12 5l7 7-7 7"/>
          </svg>
        </a>
      </div>

      <div class="l-probability" aria-label="L probability estimate">
        <span>I am va</span><span class="prob-val">L</span><span>ak. The L is not a coincidence.</span>
      </div>

      <div class="scroll-hint" aria-hidden="true">
        <span>SCROLL</span>
        <div class="scroll-arrow"></div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── Death Note Book Parallax Section ── -->
    <div class="parallax-section" aria-label="Death Note Artifact">
      <div class="parallax-bg" style="background-image: url('/assets/death_note_book.png');"></div>
      <div class="parallax-overlay">
        <p class="parallax-text">The system whose vulnerabilities are written in this notebook shall fall.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ── Section Cards ── -->
    <section class="home-sections" aria-label="Navigate to sections">
      <p class="home-sections-title">The Notebook</p>
      <div class="home-cards" role="list">

        <!-- Pentest Handbook -->
        <a href="/pentest" class="home-card" role="listitem" id="card-pentest" aria-label="Pentest Handbook">
          <span class="card-number">01</span>
          <span class="card-icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="1em" height="1em" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" fill="none"><path d="M4 19.5v-15A2.5 2.5 0 0 1 6.5 2H20v20H6.5a2.5 2.5 0 0 1 0-5H20"></path></svg>
          </span>
          <h2 class="card-title">Pentest Handbook</h2>
          <p class="card-desc">
            Every technique. Every command. Every methodology - organized by category
            and written like case notes. Red-Teaming, Web Attacks, Active Directory.
          </p>
          <span class="card-arrow">
            Open Handbook
            <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true">
              <path d="M5 12h14M12 5l7 7-7 7"/>
            </svg>
          </span>
        </a>

        <!-- CTF Case Files -->
        <a href="/ctf" class="home-card" role="listitem" id="card-ctf" aria-label="CTF Case Files">
          <span class="card-number">02</span>
          <span class="card-icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="1em" height="1em" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" fill="none"><path d="M4 15s1-1 4-1 5 2 8 2 4-1 4-1V3s-1 1-4 1-5-2-8-2-4 1-4 1z"></path><line x1="4" y1="22" x2="4" y2="15"></line></svg>
          </span>
          <h2 class="card-title">CTF Case Files</h2>
          <p class="card-desc">
            Every competition is a case. Every challenge is a suspect.
            Writeups from CTFs - documented with methodology, tools used, and lessons learned.
          </p>
          <span class="card-arrow">
            Open Case Files
            <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true">
              <path d="M5 12h14M12 5l7 7-7 7"/>
            </svg>
          </span>
        </a>

        <!-- Cyber Intel -->
        <a href="/news" class="home-card" role="listitem" id="card-news" aria-label="Cyber Intel News">
          <span class="card-number">03</span>
          <span class="card-icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="1em" height="1em" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" fill="none"><path d="M4 11a9 9 0 0 1 9 9"></path><path d="M4 4a16 16 0 0 1 16 16"></path><circle cx="5" cy="19" r="1"></circle></svg>
          </span>
          <h2 class="card-title">Cyber Intel</h2>
          <p class="card-desc">
            Daily intelligence from the field. Live cybersecurity news -
            vulnerabilities, breaches, tools, and threat reports. Refreshed automatically.
          </p>
          <span class="card-arrow">
            View Intel Feed
            <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true">
              <path d="M5 12h14M12 5l7 7-7 7"/>
            </svg>
          </span>
        </a>

      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── About Strip ── -->
    <section class="home-about" aria-label="About vaLak">
      <div class="about-l-image" aria-hidden="true">
        <img src="/assets/l_hero.png" alt="L Lawliet - vaLak" class="about-l-portrait" loading="lazy" />
      </div>
      <h2 class="about-handle">va<span class="handle-l">L</span>ak</h2>
      <p class="about-text">
        Navigating the world of ethical hacking and cybersecurity - one challenge at a time.
        This notebook documents the journey. The wins, the failures, the "aha" moments.
        Everything written in red ink, in the style of L himself.
        <br /><br />
        <em class="text-silver">"Watashi wa L desu."</em>
      </p>
    </section>

  </main>

</BaseLayout>

